-- Saudi Arabia to Send Women Athletes to Olympics
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-07-12T11:07:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/saudi-arabia-to-send-two-women-athletes-to-olympics-ioc-says.html
Two Saudi Arabian women athletes
will take part in the London 2012 games, the  International
Olympic Committee  said on its website.  Sarah Attar will run in the 800 meters and Wodjan Ali Seraj
Abdulrahim Shahrkhani is to take part in the judo event.  Saudi Arabia has previously sent all-male teams to the
Olympics.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  